Interface ICompilationUnitHandler

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractModelSynchronizer.LoaderCompilationUnitHandler, WorkspaceCUFinder.CountingCUHandler
public interface ICompilationUnitHandler

A listener for events isseud by an ICompilationUnitFinder instance during compilation unit traversals

Author:
Hristo Sabev

void finished()

handle

void handle(org.eclipse.jdt.core.ICompilationUnit cu)
Called when the ICompilationUnitFinder instance found a compilation unit. This method is awlays called after a call to handle(JavaProject). The reported compilation unit is guaranteed to be found inside the JavaProject reported by the last call to . This method will be called exactly once for each compilation unit

Parameters:
cu - - the compilation unit found by the finder

handle

void handle(org.eclipse.jdt.core.IJavaProject jprj)
Called when the ICompilationUnitFinder instance found a java project. This method is always called before the handle(ICompilationUnit) for any compilation unit found in this project. This method will be called exactly once for each found project.

Parameters:
jprj - - the java project found by the finder
